  "text": "anchor Image: © Reiulf Ramstad Arkitekter A rather hearty new community center and learning space designed for the small town of Hjørring in Denmark's North Jutland region is worth a closer look after garnering an Honor distinction from the AIA International Award program in 2024.  Image: © Reiulf Ramstad ArkitekterReiulf Ramstad Arkitekter’s Kornet Hus (or 'House of Grain') is designed for educational purposes, highlighting the role of grain production in the local economy and food culture endemic to the region.  Image: © Reiulf Ramstad ArkitekterImage: © Reiulf Ramstad ArkitekterBrick and GLT timber/wood are used as the primary building materials in a gesture that reinterprets the sight of a traditional baker’s kiln. Interiors are clad in oak paneling. The project was realized in 2020 at roughly 7,300 square feet (680 square meters), and infused an acoustically enhancing dot pattern lining its walls as part of its architectural composition.  Image: © Reiulf Ramstad ArkitekterA large bread oven itself forms the focal point of public activities for the center, around which various culinary workshops and demonstrations can be configured under strategically positioned lightwells.  Image: © Reiulf Ramstad ArkitekterThe experience inside ends in vistas opening out onto the landscape and adjoining Kornets Hage (aka the 'Garden of Grain'), a large expanse of wheatfields that was planted after completion and unfurls to the west, framed by circulatory routes leading to a carefully staged terrace. Image: © Reiulf Ramstad ArkitekterThe design also received a 2022 AZ Award in addition to its AIA Honor Award and win in the same competition’s Sustainable Future Award category last year. The practice says each \"reinforces\" their belief in architecture’s power to connect communities and ultimately \"do good for the planet.\" Reiulf Ramstad Arkitekter is headquartered in Oslo and was founded by Reiulf Ramstad in 1995.",
  "image": "https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/9c/9cc0ced0cea3baf33818f387fb5f55b9.jpg?fit=crop\u0026auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026enlarge=true\u0026crop=faces\u0026w=1200\u0026h=707",
  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\n      \t\t\t\t\t\u003cul\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003cli id=\"Entry1\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cspan\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003ca name=\"entry\" id=\"EntryAnchor\"\u003eanchor\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cdiv\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/9c/9cc0ced0cea3baf33818f387fb5f55b9.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\" title=\"Image: © Reiulf Ramstad Arkitekter\" data-size=\"4798x3199\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cimg srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/9c/9cc0ced0cea3baf33818f387fb5f55b9.jpg?fit=crop\u0026amp;auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/9c/9cc0ced0cea3baf33818f387fb5f55b9.jpg?fit=crop\u0026amp;auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/9c/9cc0ced0cea3baf33818f387fb5f55b9.jpg?fit=crop\u0026amp;auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\" src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/9c/9cc0ced0cea3baf33818f387fb5f55b9.jpg?fit=crop\u0026amp;auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" title=\"Image: © Reiulf Ramstad Arkitekter\" alt=\"Image: © Reiulf Ramstad Arkitekter\" width=\"514\" height=\"\"/\u003e\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eImage: © Reiulf Ramstad Arkitekter\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cdiv\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003eA rather hearty new community center and learning space designed for the small town of Hjørring in \u003ca href=\"https://archinect.com/news/tag/3692/denmark\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eDenmark\u003c/a\u003e\u0026#39;s North Jutland region is worth a closer look after garnering an Honor distinction from the \u003ca href=\"https://archinect.com/news/bustler/10155/the-2024-aia-international-design-awards-crown-the-best-new-member-designs-globally\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eAIA International Award program\u003c/a\u003e in 2024. \u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/26/26ef7099dc11362fd3d83a30bba82741.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x685\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/26/26ef7099dc11362fd3d83a30bba82741.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/26/26ef7099dc11362fd3d83a30bba82741.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/26/26ef7099dc11362fd3d83a30bba82741.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/26/26ef7099dc11362fd3d83a30bba82741.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: © Reiulf Ramstad Arkitekter\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eReiulf Ramstad Arkitekter’s Kornet Hus (or \u0026#39;House of Grain\u0026#39;) is designed for educational purposes, highlighting the role of grain production in the local economy and food culture endemic to the region. \u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/b0/b07b1ee3e66bcd430e126498f502bf3e.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x685\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/b0/b07b1ee3e66bcd430e126498f502bf3e.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/b0/b07b1ee3e66bcd430e126498f502bf3e.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/b0/b07b1ee3e66bcd430e126498f502bf3e.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/b0/b07b1ee3e66bcd430e126498f502bf3e.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: © Reiulf Ramstad Arkitekter\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/52/522d84b6224c3f851d41381400118208.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x685\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/52/522d84b6224c3f851d41381400118208.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/52/522d84b6224c3f851d41381400118208.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/52/522d84b6224c3f851d41381400118208.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/52/522d84b6224c3f851d41381400118208.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: © Reiulf Ramstad Arkitekter\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eBrick and GLT timber/wood are used as the primary building materials in a gesture that reinterprets the sight of a traditional baker’s kiln. Interiors are clad in oak paneling. The project was realized in 2020 at roughly 7,300 square feet (680 square meters), and infused an acoustically enhancing dot pattern lining its walls as part of its architectural composition. \u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/71/7124e81938ce9222a2e499b1c8c5a993.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x952\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/71/7124e81938ce9222a2e499b1c8c5a993.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/71/7124e81938ce9222a2e499b1c8c5a993.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/71/7124e81938ce9222a2e499b1c8c5a993.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/71/7124e81938ce9222a2e499b1c8c5a993.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: © Reiulf Ramstad Arkitekter\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eA large bread oven itself forms the focal point of public activities for the center, around which various culinary workshops and demonstrations can be configured under strategically positioned lightwells. \u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/5c/5c893be262a44186829c0038ae06e121.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x1343\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/5c/5c893be262a44186829c0038ae06e121.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/5c/5c893be262a44186829c0038ae06e121.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/5c/5c893be262a44186829c0038ae06e121.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/5c/5c893be262a44186829c0038ae06e121.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: © Reiulf Ramstad Arkitekter\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe experience inside ends in vistas opening out onto the landscape and adjoining Kornets Hage (aka the \u0026#39;Garden of Grain\u0026#39;), a large expanse of wheatfields that was planted after completion and unfurls to the west, framed by circulatory routes leading to a carefully staged terrace.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/75/75ca43f17b381f3decde6c56c9ff967e.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x1542\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/75/75ca43f17b381f3decde6c56c9ff967e.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/75/75ca43f17b381f3decde6c56c9ff967e.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/75/75ca43f17b381f3decde6c56c9ff967e.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/75/75ca43f17b381f3decde6c56c9ff967e.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: © Reiulf Ramstad Arkitekter\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe design also received a \u003ca href=\"https://archinect.com/news/article/150315996/co-adaptive-omar-gandhi-architect-and-reiulf-ramstad-arkitekter-among-winners-of-the-2022-az-awards\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e2022 AZ Award\u003c/a\u003e in addition to its AIA Honor Award and win in the same competition’s Sustainable Future Award category last year. The practice says each \u0026#34;reinforces\u0026#34; their belief in architecture’s power to connect communities and ultimately \u0026#34;do good for the planet.\u0026#34; Reiulf Ramstad Arkitekter is headquartered in Oslo and was founded by Reiulf Ramstad in 1995.\u003c/p\u003e\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cbr clear=\"all\"/\u003e\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ca name=\"comments\" id=\"CommentsAnchor\"\u003e \u003c/a\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/ul\u003e\n\t  \t\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
